/* 

    ====================
        Installation
    ====================

1. npm init
2. npm install node-sass --save-dev ==> devdependencies
3. npm install node-sass --save (optional) ==> dependencies


    ====================
        Compilation
    ====================
1. update package.json file --> scripts attribute
2. package-name  input-file output-file --> node-sass main.scss style.css
3. npm run compile:sass (Terminal)

To keep tracks for any updates that you make it on sass file , you should re-compile it again after each update, but this is not practical
So, update package.json file to keep watching

Then :  npm run compile:sass (once)


Note: npm install live-server (To automatically reloading the page for any file changes)
 ==> install it gloabally --> for any project in my PC not a particualr project
npm install live-server -g 

 */
